Fitting a model

X <- model.matrix(object=BirthWeight ~ ., data=baby)
y <- baby$BirthWeight

B <- solve((t(X)%*%X)) %*% t(X) %*% y
s_squared <- (t(y-X%*%B) %*% (y-X%*%B))/(nrow(baby)-ncol(X))

# My B
print(B)
##                     [,1]
## (Intercept) -4120.542409
## Mage           -3.793751
## Gage          182.742497
## Racehisp      198.747954
## Raceother     241.582827
## Racewhite     204.888197
## GenMale      -169.348562
# My s^2
print(s_squared)
##          [,1]
## [1,] 79277.09
baby.lm <- lm(formula=BirthWeight ~ ., data=baby)

# lm's B
print(coef(baby.lm))
##  (Intercept)         Mage         Gage     Racehisp    Raceother    Racewhite 
## -4120.542409    -3.793751   182.742497   198.747954   241.582827   204.888197 
##      GenMale 
##  -169.348562
# lm's s^2
print(sigma(baby.lm)**2)
## [1] 79277.09
fitted_vals <- X %*% B

# My fitted values
print(head(fitted_vals))
##       [,1]
## 1 2954.698
## 2 3074.728
## 3 2716.497
## 4 3502.926
## 5 2922.336
## 6 3245.756
# lm's fitted values
print(head(fitted(baby.lm)))
##        1        2        3        4        5        6 
## 2954.698 3074.728 2716.497 3502.926 2922.336 3245.756
resids <- y - fitted_vals

# My residuals
print(head(resids))
##         [,1]
## 1   72.27167
## 2  158.38188
## 3  -72.10682
## 4  497.52418
## 5  359.15436
## 6 -496.87555
# lm's residuals
print(head(resid(baby.lm)))
##          1          2          3          4          5          6 
##   72.27167  158.38188  -72.10682  497.52418  359.15436 -496.87555
summary(baby.lm)$r.squared
## [1] 0.6064689
